response: * Helen Sear (born 1955), a Welsh photographic artist

MacDonald was until September 2016 co-director, alongside Stuart Smith, of the visual arts publisher GOST."Gordon MacDonald and GOST", GOST, 14 September 2016. Accessed 22 January 2020. GOST published Mass by Mark Power, Brisees by Helen Sear, Chateau Despair and Hyenas of the Battlefield, Machines in the Garden by Lisa Barnard, UKG by Ewen Spencer, Skirts by Clare Strand, Spill by Daniel Beltra, Maidan – Portraits from the Black Square by Anastasia Taylor-Lind, The Winners by Rafał Milach, Punks by Karen Knorr and Oliver Richon and Hong Kong Parr by Martin Parr.
